<section class="hero">
  <h1>Discount, or <em>Premium?</em></h1>
  <div class="hero-subtitle">Bitcoin runs above and below its long-run trend &mdash; sometimes far above, sometimes far below.</div>
  <p class="subtitle">This page tells you, live, <em>which one is true right now</em> &mdash; and what returning to trend would mean.</p>
</section>

<main class="content-area">

  {% include 'components/tool-framing.njk' %}

  <div class="section-intro dp-prose">
    <p>Most people think in CAGR. The Power Law doesn&rsquo;t: it describes a <em>declining</em> growth rate along a rising trend, with price oscillating around that trend rather than tracking it. So the useful question is not &ldquo;what return does bitcoin give&rdquo; but a two-part one: <strong>where is price relative to trend right now</strong>, and <strong>what would returning to that trend imply</strong>?</p>
    <p>Below trend, reversion implies an elevated near-term CAGR &mdash; the &ldquo;discount&rdquo; case. Above trend, the identical arithmetic implies a depressed or negative one. Both come out of the same formula with no special-casing, which is the point: this is an instrument, not a pitch. It would have said harsh things at every past top, and <a href="#backtest">it still does</a>.</p>
  </div>

